	    		<h1>Will</h1>
	    		<h3>What is it?</h3>
	    		<h5>A will is a legal document that sets forth your wishes regarding the distribution of your property and the care of any minor children. To maximize the likelihood that your wishes are carried out, you want a will that is set forth in writing, and signed by you and your witnesses. If your will does not meet those basic standards, your instructions may not be carried out or hold up in court!</h5>
	    		<h3>How can it benefit me?</h3>
	    		<h5>Creating a will give you sole discretion over the distribution of your assets. It lets you decide how your belongings, such as cars or family heirlooms should be distributed. Especially if you have a business or investments a will can help that transfer process go much easier!</h5>
	  		</div>
