	    		<h1>Living Will</h1>
	    		<h3>What is it?</h3>
	    		<h5>A living will is completely different from a regular will. The living will is mainly used for "end-of-life" medical care. In case something was to happen to you and you are unable to communicate your decisions, the living will would then take effect. Living wills have no authority after death, after that it would then go to a regular will for any correspondence from there on out.</h5>
	    		<h3>How can it benefit me?</h3>
	    		<h5>Having a living will can take a lot of the stress off your family if anything were to ever happen to you. Family members for the most part may not be able to make a logical decision in the time of crisis. Which can result in a giant financial burden for you and your family.</h5>
