	    		<h3>How can it benefit me?</h3>
	    		<h5>Having a power of attorney can benefit you in multiple areas. The first of which would provide you will the ability to choose who will make decisions for you (rather than a court). Provides family members an opportunity to discuss wishes and desires for next steps. It can prevent delays in asset protection planning which can be a very stressful situation. Most of all, it provides you and your family the peace of mind that you have a person of law on your side in times of hardship for your family.</h5>
